 >The driver installation tested HDD and set the speed to # 7.  The manual
 >says the max speed # is 8 for Mode 3.  That meant the card could not get
 >full Mode 3 speed.

The install utility is rather conservative, it sets the driver one
_slower_ than the highest rate that tested correctly. In other words, if
the driver is set to speed #7 that means that your drive tested
correctly at #8. If you feel adventurous, you could try setting #8
manually, but I should warn you that it _might_ be a tiny bit too fast
for the drive resulting in occasional flakiness. This is precisely the
reason why the install utility sets the speed one notch lower.

 >The manual lacks some tech specs such as onboard BIOS size (I guess 16Kb)

Yes.

 >2 IDE's address.

What was it, 1F0/IRQ14 and 170/IRQ15? Completely standard anyway.

 >The card does let you change the BIOS address but the system would
 >refuse to boot up if you do not use the default.

Strange. I immediately set it at C800 to avoid splitting up my UMBs,
and it works fine.

 >The card does support 2.88 FD but the default jumper setting is for
 >1.2/1.44 only. Somebody told me it does not work w/ 2.88 FD.  

I don't know about floppies, but my tapedrive definitely has doubled its
